{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_22","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc 'rg -n -C 4 \"undefined scheme|WebClientAutoConfiguration|all seven tests failing|reactiveHttpServiceClientAutoConfigurationAppliesPropertiesAndCustomizers|ImportHttpServiceRegistrar|No tests or metadata files were modified|metadata_fix_failed|apply_patch verification failed\" human-intervention-logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-webclient:4.1.0-RC1/metadata-fix/codex.log post-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md human-intervention-logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-webclient:4.1.0-RC1/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-06-26T22-50-50-453716Z.log'","aggregated_output":"human-intervention-logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-webclient:4.1.0-RC1/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-06-26T22-50-50-453716Z.log-1-Wrote the intervention report:\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-webclient:4.1.0-RC1/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-06-26T22-50-50-453716Z.log-2-\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-webclient:4.1.0-RC1/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-06-26T22-50-50-453716Z.log-3-`post-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md`\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-webclient:4.1.0-RC1/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-06-26T22-50-50-453716Z.log-4-\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-webclient:4.1.0-RC1/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-06-26T22-50-50-453716Z.log:5:No tests or metadata files were modified. The failures were classified as metadata-related / incomplete metadata repair, so the generated tests were preserved.\n--\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-1-# Post-generation intervention report\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-2-\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-3-Library: org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-webclient:4.1.0-RC1\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md:4:Stage: metadata_fix_failed\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-5-\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-6-## Summary\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-7-\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md:8:The native test run failed in generated Spring Boot WebClient tests. The Gradle excerpt shows all seven tests failing while Spring Boot tries to read annotation metadata for `org.springframework.boot.webclient.autoconfigure.WebClientAutoConfiguration` and cannot open the corresponding classpath resource. This is a metadata/resource-registration problem, not unsupported native-image behavior.\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-9-\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md:10:The Codex metadata-fix log shows that Codex partially repaired earlier native-image gaps: it added class-resource, reflection, and proxy-related coverage and got six of the seven tests passing in a later run. The remaining failure in the log is `reactiveHttpServiceClientAutoConfigurationAppliesPropertiesAndCustomizers()`, where the generated HTTP service client is created but the configured `base-url` is not applied, producing `java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: URI with undefined scheme`.\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-11-\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-12-## Root cause classification\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-13-\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-14-- `autoConfigurationsAreAdvertisedForSpringBootDiscovery()` — metadata-related. Spring Boot discovery requires `META-INF/spring/org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.AutoConfiguration.imports` and the referenced auto-configuration class resources in the native image.\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md:15:- `webClientAutoConfigurationCreatesPrototypeBuilderWithConnectorAndCustomizers()` — metadata-related in the provided Gradle excerpt because the shared `ApplicationContextRunner` auto-configuration path cannot read `WebClientAutoConfiguration.class` as a resource.\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-16-- `webClientCodecCustomizerAppliesBootCodecCustomizersToClientBuilder()` — no unsupported native behavior was identified; Codex later got this support passing.\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-17-- `observationWebClientCustomizerRecordsClientObservationsWithConfiguredConvention()` — metadata-related in the provided Gradle excerpt through Spring Boot auto-configuration metadata/resource loading; Codex later got this support passing.\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-18-- `webClientObservationAutoConfigurationCreatesCustomizerWhenObservationRegistryIsAvailable()` — metadata-related; Spring Boot cannot inspect the WebClient auto-configuration class resource in the failing native image.\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md:19:- `reactiveHttpServiceClientAutoConfigurationAppliesPropertiesAndCustomizers()` — still unresolved after Codex's partial metadata repair. The log shows earlier missing metadata for `ImportHttpServiceRegistrar`, the HTTP service proxy, and related Spring HTTP-service classes was addressed, but the final native run still did not apply `spring.http.serviceclient.catalog.base-url`. This points to remaining Spring Boot HTTP-service-client metadata around native resource/reflection/conditional processing or property binding, not to bytecode generation, instrumentation, inline/static mocking, self-attach, or another unsupported native-image feature.\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md:20:- `webClientSslAppliesNamedSslBundleToWebClientBuilder()` — metadata-related in the provided Gradle excerpt because context startup reaches Spring Boot auto-configuration metadata reading and fails on the missing `WebClientAutoConfiguration.class` resource.\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-21-\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-22-## Metadata still missing or incomplete\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-23-\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md:24:The immediate Gradle excerpt indicates missing native-image resource metadata for Spring Boot auto-configuration class resources, specifically `org/springframework/boot/webclient/autoconfigure/WebClientAutoConfiguration.class`. Codex's later attempts also showed missing resource coverage for `org/springframework/web/service/registry/ImportHttpServiceRegistrar.class` and missing proxy/reflection metadata for the generated HTTP service client path before those were partially addressed.\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md-25-\npost-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-webclient_4.1.0-RC1.md:26:Codex did not finish resolving the final HTTP-service-client property binding/configurer path. After the explicit proxy failure was gone, the remaining `URI with undefined scheme` failure means the `CatalogClient` request was issued against `/items` without the configured server `base-url`. The log ended while Codex was still investigating whether Spring's `@ConditionalOnBean(HttpServicePro